The description of the growths as painless and slowly increasing in size suggests that the most likely diagnosis is genital warts caused by human papillomavirus (HPV). Cryotherapy, which involves freezing the warts with liquid nitrogen, is a common treatment for genital warts. Interferon, laser therapy, and topical imiquimod are also options for treating genital warts, but cryotherapy is the most appropriate initial management.
